# Interactive cursor (pointer)

- **Theme:** `src/theme_cursor.rs` appends GTK CSS `cursor` rules only when `gtk::check_version(4, 16, 0)` passes at runtime (4.14.x on Ubuntu still logs “No property named cursor”). **macOS:** omitted (Homebrew GTK rejects `cursor` in CSS). Do not add theme rules that set a pointer on `entry`, `textview`, or the video `GLArea` (leave default / I‑beam / system).
- **Code:** For a new control that is not covered by those GTK node types (e.g. a custom hit target), call `set_cursor_from_name(Some("pointer"))` on the widget (see `recent_view` undo bar). For disabled custom controls, use `None` or an appropriate cursor.
- **Continue cards** already set pointer on hover via `EventControllerMotion`; on Linux, global button CSS also applies to icon buttons on cards.
